        <h2>Why UAE Visas Require Birth Certificate Translation</h2>

        <p>When you apply for a UAE visa or residence permit, immigration authorities need to verify your identity and family relationships. Your birth certificate establishes your date of birth, nationality at birth, and parentage. <strong>Arabic is the official language of UAE government agencies</strong>, so all supporting documents must be in Arabic or translated into Arabic.</p>

