        <p>If your name includes characters that don't have direct Arabic equivalents, the translator uses standard transliteration conventions. Ensure this matches how your name appears on your passport.</p>

        <h3>Multi-Page or Supplementary Documents</h3>

        <p>Some countries issue birth certificates with supplementary pages—amendments, name changes, or additional certifications. All pages require translation. Don't leave out supplementary sheets thinking they're not important.</p>

        <h3>Birth Certificates Without English</h3>

        <p>If your birth certificate is in a language other than English (and you need the translation for a DIFC or ADGM matter, or for an embassy that works in English), you may need translation into both English and Arabic. Clarify the requirement with the receiving authority.</p>

